steak and kidney pie

needs:
- 2tbsp oil
- 30g flour
- ~500ml stock
- 700g beef
- 200g kidney
- 2 onions
- mashing veg (potatoes, carrots)

steps:
- brown beef and kidneys.
- add onions.
- mix in flour.
- add stock
- simmer for ~60-90 minutes on a low heat.
- mix in some salt, pepper, and Worcestershire.
- top with mash, bake.

notes:
- makes 4 servings.
- really you want ~900g meat in some ratio, e.g. 500g kidney 400g beef.
- probably also want to add more veg (mushrooms, leeks?) to the pie mix.
